<TEXT>
a federal grand jury will investigate a 
weekend clash in which vietnamese immigrants and longtime louisiana 
shrimp fishermen exchanged gunfire and rammed each others boats 
the fbi said monday 
we turned the results of our investigation over to the us 
attorney those results will be presented to a grand jury and any 
criminal charges that result will come out of that investigation 
said fbi spokesman volney hayes 
no injuries were reported in the saturday gun battle at whiskey 
pass one of louisianas barrier islands in the gulf of mexico 
about 75 miles southwest of new orleans 
six shrimp boats some with bullet holes were taken to the 
small fishing community of port fourchon on sunday the coast guard 
said after crew members were questioned the boats were released 
a spokesman for the harbor police said 
four vietnamese fishermen were detained for their own safety but 
no one was arrested the coast guard said they were interviewed by 
federal agents sunday at grand isle then returned to their boat 
sunday afternoon 
the vietnamese fishermen would not discuss the incident with 
reporters who gathered sunday at port fourchon louisiana fishermen 
said the vietnamese shot first the coast guard said the shooting 
broke out after the anchor of the vessel our mama manned by 
longtime louisiana fishermen became entangled in the net of the 
vessel freedom i manned by vietnamese living in the united states 
</TEXT>
