<TEXT>
a fundamentalist moslem guerrilla 
leader threatened to fight against any superpower deal to end the 
12yearold struggle to oust afghanistans promoscow government 
gulbuddin hekmatyar firebrand leader of hezbiislami or party 
of islam has vowed to launch a jihad or holy war if a dealis 
worked out at this months ussoviet summit in washington 
the afghan war is expected to figure prominently in talks 
beginning may 30 between president bush and soviet president 
mikhail s gorbachev 
the superpowers have agreed to prevent the formation of an 
islamic government in afghanistan said abdul qadir karyab who 
heads hekmatyars politicial committee 
we will not only continue our jihad on the battlefield but we 
also have other ways should the superpowers interfere in our 
internal affairs karyab told the associated press 
western diplomats and afghan experts in islamabad have hinted 
the superpowers are close to a deal but decline to give any 
specific details 
the likeliest scenario they said was have elections in 
afghanistan run jointly by the united nations and the organization 
of the islamic conference or by a neutral group chosen by the two 
organizations 
but they also warned it will be very difficult to find a 
political solution acceptable to both the rebels and the afghan 
government 
afghan president najibullah has refused to step down prior to 
elections a precondition set by even the most moderate guerrilla 
groups headquartered in pakistans rugged frontier city of peshawar 
the guerrillas have come under increasing pressure particularly 
from the united states to end their internal rivalries and devise 
a political settlement to the war 
but the seven guerrilla groups are deeply divided the president 
of the guerrillas selfproclaimed governmentinexile 
sibghatullah mojaddidi has branded hekmatyar a murderer and 
accused him of killing more innocent afghans than soviet or afghan 
soldiers 
karyab said the hezbiislami would consider imposing its will 
on the other guerrilla groups 
if they cant agree with our reasonable proposals we have our 
unreasonable ways he said refusing to elaborate 
hekmatyar is also feuding with burhanuddin rabbani leader of 
the powerful jamiatiislami or society of islam the two have 
traded threats and accusations of murder kidnapping and theft 
hekmatyar who is strongly antiwestern fought ferociously 
against the soviets and received the lions share of us military 
assistance during the 12yearold war 
karyab said washington now fears hekmatyars strength in 
afghanistan 
as far as i can see the united states has very dangerous 
plans including certain activity even terrorist acts against the 
hezbiislami leader karyab said 
the united states sends 500 million a year in aid to the 
guerrillas while the soviet union gives an estimated 5 billion a 
year to the kabul government 
</TEXT>
