northwest of bucharest and 300 were injured before the army could 
restore order 
representatives of romanias 22 million hungarians say their 
struggle for minority rights is being suppressed as it was under 
ceausescu 
part of the support for iliescu rests on the interim 
governments ability to provide relative plenty after years of 
privation under ceausescu who starved the people to pay off the 
foreign debt with exports 
generous foreign aid an end to food exports increased energy 
imports and mild weather since february have kept people fed and 
warm but luxury items such as chocolate and citrus fruits are in 
short supply 
