the president of the world jewish congress 
said today that economic hardship in eastern europe was causing a 
rise in antisemitism 
the congress is holding its first meeting ever on german soil 
and president edgar m bronfman acknowledged that some delegates 
had declined to attend the threeday conference because of berlins 
strong links to the nazi past 
bronfman told the 500 delegates at sundays opening session that 
a united germany must forever teach about the nazi slaughter of 
6 million jews nearly twothirds of european jewry he called the 
holocaust the lowest point ever reached in mans inhumanity to 
man 
at a news conference today he expressed concern for the 
survivors of eastern europes once vibrant jewish community and for 
the nearly 15 million jews in the soviet union 
these countries are trying to introduce democratic changes at a 
time of economic difficulties and bronfman said jews once again 
face being singled out for attack 
referring to antisemitic tendencies in such countries as the 
soviet union and east germany bronfman cited attempts to revive 
the ageold scapegoat the jew during economic hard times 
we dont like it bronfman told the new conference at the 
west berlin jewish community building the only way to fight it 
is to expose it 
he said he had received personal assurances from soviet foreign 
minister eduard shevardnadze that law enforcement officials will 
