baghdad to amman jordan today after lengthy talks with the iraqi 
president he met assad in damascus saturday 
abdullah met with king hussein in amman the monarch who has 
also sought to mediate an end to the 11yearold break between 
syria and iraq is a close ally of saddam 
a senior jordanian official said on condition of anonymity we 
believe an arab summit will be convened for sure this month in 
baghdad 
all the indications are that a summit will take place 
especially after saudi arabia announced it will attend he said 
assads dispute with iraq and his 7yearold feud with plo 
chairman yasser arafat are the main obstacles to arab efforts 
toward a new unity 
arafat has been at odds with syria since 1983 when syrianbacked 
radical palestinian factions mutinied against him and drove his 
guerrillas out of their last lebanese stronghold 
assad has not recognized the palestinian state declared in 
1988 and still holds 2000 of arafats loyalists in his prisons 
syria and iraq have been at odds since 1979 the countries are 
ruled by different wings of the arab baath socialist party and are 
rivals for political leadership of the modern arab world 
arafat in april called for the summit to be held in baghdad to 
discuss mass soviet jewish emigration to israel middle east peace 
moves and the crisis in lebanon 
