the hired assassin who almost succeeded in 
killing french president charles de gaulle in 1962 says disgruntled 
french officers planned to kidnap try and then execute the general 
in an interview published sunday in the daily el pais georges 
henri watin better known as the jackal said the plan went 
awry before he shot at de gaulle in his presidential vehicle in the 
french village of petit clamart 
the incident was dramatized in a 1971 novel by frederick 
forsythe called the day of the jackal it was later made into a 
film 
watin now a paraguayan citizen who claims to live 
handtomouth said the novelistic version of the aug 22 1962 
plot bears no relation to what really happened 
reality is too dramatic i know my own story and one thing i 
have to make clear is that there was never a plan simply to kill 
the old man in petit clamart the plan was to kidnap him bring 
him to justice before a military courtmartial and only then 
execute him watin said 
de gualle was to be tried for his support of algerias 
independence from france 
watin said the plan was to kidnap de gaulle at sunset but the 
officers who did the figuring used an almanac from the previous 
year and got the time wrong the presidential cortege arrived 
earlier than expected 
suddenly i realized that the whole plan should be scrapped 
immediately watin said but by then it was too late 
watin said he and the two other hired guns shot at the rear 
window of de gaulles car and at the two rear tires 
for a moment i looked directly at his de gaulles eyes our 
car was right alongside his but we had calculated shooting at a 
car that was practically immobile watin said later i learned 
i had missed him by just two centimeters 
de gaulle was harshly criticized in the early 1960s for favoring 
the independence of algeria in april 1961 four french generals 
based in algiers and belonging to the secret army organization 
staged an abortive coup against de gaulles government 
shortly after the petit clamart attack de gaulle announced 
algeria deserved to become independent on july 3 1962 he 
proclaimed algeria a sovereign nation 
