when the exclusive inn at little 
washington opened in an abandoned garage in 1978 some of the 250 
residents of this northwestern virginia hamlet considered its 
nameplate well belittling 
the sign and the residents fury eventually faded 
but now the awardwinning inn some of whose celebrity guests 
travel the 67 miles from washington dc by helicopter is again 
provoking the wrath of neighbors who fear for the towns seclusion 
and its 200yearold heritage 
the mobil travel guide ranks it as the only fivestar inn in the 
country craig claiborne former food columnist of the new york 
times called it one of the most exciting retreats in all of 
