chinese authorities in tibet announced strict new 
controls monday on foreign travel to the region saying each 
traveler must submit an application in advance to local authorities 
the new rules apply even to ordinary tourists making it 
unlikely that tourism will get back to the levels of before march 
1989 when martial law was imposed to end proindependence rioting 
martial law was lifted just last week 
the official xinhua news agency quoted tang zhengqi deputy 
secretarygeneral of the regional government as saying the 
controls were imposed because tibet has limited capacity to 
accommodate foreign travelers 
