<TEXT>
convoys of khmer rouge trucks 
filled with the recent rice harvest move freely through this rural 
village in northwest cambodia and young guerrilla fighters flirt 
with relaxed villagers 
we are very happy to be back in our country said khmer 
rouge division commander mit soe over coconut juice as cambodian 
government artillery rumbled in the distance 
in a scene played out in scores of villages in rural cambodia in 
recent months pol pots khmer rouge have returned to areas they 
were driven out of when vietnamese forces invaded cambodia in late 
1978 and installed a prohanoi government 
to much of the world the khmer rouge are fanatics who killed 
hundreds of thousands of their countrymen during the 1970s in a 
savage bid to create a communist agrarian society 
but despite the widely held perception that they continue to be 
universally despised the khmer rouge maintain significant and 
increasing support in the longneglected poor villages of this 
ravaged country 
since the announced pullout of vietnamese troops in september 
the khmer rouge have seized hundreds of villages in the north west 
and southwest of the country 
khmer rouge officials in cambodia and western intelligence 
sources in bangkok thailand say the group is attracting followers 
by tapping the deep suspicion most cambodians harbor for their 
historical enemy vietnam 
the khmer rouge contend that vietnam intends to swallow 
cambodia they allege that despite the pledged vietnamese 
withdrawal vietnamese troops secretly remain in cambodia disguised 
as cambodian soldiers 
although human rights groups have described strict regimentation 
and brutality in khmer rougecontrolled areas over the past decade 
the guerrillas seem to have abandoned their harshest practices at 
least temporarily 
analysts are quick to point out that most cambodians still 
loathe the khmer rouge and note that pol pot khieu samphan and 
other leaders who presided over the 197578 reign of terror are 
still in charge there is fear that if the khmer rouge were to 
return to power their murderous ways would simply resurface 
but the analysts say the khmer rouge have managed to maintain a 
support network throughout rural cambodia and have been able to 
recruit fighters since being driven to sanctuaries along the 
thaicambodian border after the vietnamese invasion 
if they were that evil they wouldnt have survived the last 
11 years there must be something they are fighting for that makes 
the khmer people join them singapore prime minister lee kuan yew 
told the british newspaper the independent in a recent interview 
although he frequently condemns the khmer rouge cambodias 
exiled leader prince norodom sihanouk recently said they have 
adopted a new style that includes scrupulously honest and 
disciplined behavior when dealing with villagers 
sihanouk who ruled cambodia until he was ousted in a 1970 
military coup predicted the khmer rouge would win many seats 
in parliament should general elections be held in cambodia 
you wont get people to vote for pol pot himself for 
president said one western intelligence analyst in bangkok 
speaking on condition of anonymity but as an organization they 
have clear popular support based on their honesty dedication and 
nationalism 
by contrast the prohanoi government in phnom penh and the two 
noncommunist guerrilla groups which are loosely allied with the 
khmer rouge are rife with the decadeslong scourge of cambodian 
politics corruption 
in recent months soldiers of the two noncommunist groups have 
also displayed a gross lack of discipline that has shocked even 
their own commanders rape and robbery of villagers occur 
frequently 
when the khmer rouge come to town you dont have to hide your 
daughter and your money said a bangkokbased diplomat 
requesting anonymity 
in the un refugee camps that house 300000 
guerrillacontrolled civilians along the thai border relief 
officials say the khmer rouge camps are the bestrun 
we have the least problems in the khmer rouge camps said a 
senior un official in the border town of aranyaprathet a lot 
less corruption their leaders are hardworking and dedicated 
nobody wants to hear it but it happens to be true he spoke on 
condition he not be identified 
western and thai intelligence sources say that as many as 80 
percent of the khmer rouge ranks are new recruits who have joined 
since the vietnamese invasion troop strength is generally 
estimated at between 25000 and 35000 more than twice the size of 
the decimated forces which fled to the thai border in 1979 
dozens of khmer rouge fighters interviewed in recent weeks in 
newly seized villages in northwest cambodia say they considered 
themselves nationalists and openly rejected communism 
the average khmer rouge soldier thinks he is liberating his 
country from the vietnamese not fighting for an ideology said 
one western diplomat in bangkok requesting anonymity 
the khmer rouge which receives chinese support says it will 
continue fighting until there is an internationally verified 
withdrawal of vietnamese troops and a coalition government 
including the three guerrilla groups and the prohanoi government 
of prime minister hun sen 
the phnom penh government has rejected any interim coalition 
including the khmer rouge which it accuses of genocide against the 
cambodian people 
