jurors were urged monday to return a murder 
verdict against a white man accused of shooting a black teenager 
who ventured into a mostlywhite neighborhood and encountered an 
angry mob 
the attack blamed on defendant joseph fama stirred racial 
tension in the brooklyn neighborhood where the slaying occurred and 
throughout the city 
the victim yusuf hawkins 16 went to the bensonhurst 
neighborhood aug 23 with two friends looking for a used car and 
was beset by a group of batwielding white youths hawkins was shot 
through the chest 
when the mob turned that corner what did they know about yusuf 
hawkins asked the prosecutor assistant district attorney edward 
boyar they knew the color of his skin that was the only thing 
they knew about yusuf hawkins 
pointing across the courtroom at the 19yearold defendant 
during his closing argument the prosecutor said the evidence 
clearly and beyond a reasonable doubt proves joseph fama was the 
one who took a gun and pointed it at the body of yusuf hawkins 
and with a wanton disregard for human life shot again and again and 
again 
