mondello also charged with two counts of seconddegree murder 
were scheduled for tuesday the two were tried in the same 
courtroom but with different juries six other youths are to be 
tried later 
the judge rejected a lastminute effort to reopen the defense 
case by depetris who said a key prosecution witness franklin 
tighe was prepared to recant his earlier testimony 
tighe a 20yearold bensonhurst resident with a long history of 
mental illness including hallucinations was the only witness to 
say he saw fama pull an automatic pistol and shoot hawkins 
since taking the witness stand on april 27 depetris said tighe 
contacted him and said he wasnt standing next to fama when hawkins 
was shot as he had testified 
its too late now the judge said in refusing to allow 
tighe who was waiting outside the courtroom to take the stand 
the whole thing sounds suspicious to me 
the exchange took place outside the presence of the jury 
after owens refused to reopen the trial depetris showed 
reporters a 26minute videotaped interview of tighe in which the 
witness says he wasnt standing next to fama 
depetris told the jury tighe believed what he was saying when he 
testified but he said that the stress of coming upon hawkins who 
was dying on the street triggered hallucinations in the mentally 
unstable man 
