leaders discussed who would be involved in talks with the 
administration and when the discussions would start 
asked if the members at the meeting agreed that negotiations 
should begin mitchell said various opinions were expressed 
house speaker thomas s foley dwash said he believed 
congressional democrats would inform the white house about their 
desires by wednesday 
senate finance committee chairman lloyd bentsen dtexas said 
he was willing to consider new levies including excise taxes and 
