the socialists italys no 3 party scored gains according to 
early results and to projections on state tvs evening newscasts 
more than eight hours after polls closed 
local parties demanding greater regional autonomy in lombardy 
and veneto in the north showed surprising success 
up for election were 15 of 20 regional governments 87 
provincial governing councils and 6374 city governments city 
elections were not being held in such major centers as rome 
naples trieste catania and bolzano 
by 10 pm results were complete in twothirds of the 
precincts complete official results were expected tuesday 
the elections were considered an important barometer of support 
for the governing coalition which includes christian democrats and 
socialists and for the communists who decided on a new course at 
an extraordinary congress in march 
with 49267 of 73965 precincts reporting the communists had 24 
percent down from 302 percent in regional elections five years 
ago and from 278 percent in parliamentary voting in 1987 
christian democrats had 338 percent down from 35 percent five 
years ago and from 342 percent in the 1987 parliamentary vote 
the socialists had 147 percent up from 133 percent and 143 
percent respectively 
the communist party has been steadily losing strength after 
coming to the brink of power a decade ago it decided to enter a 
transition phase that could lead to changing its name and dropping 
its hammerandsickle symbol 
