not alter the communist reformist course to do otherwise would 
be catastrophic he said 
he indicated the decline reflected the beatings taken by eastern 
european leftist parties in recent elections following the toppling 
over the past year of communists regimes there 
final projections indicated the communists would get 236 
percent down from 302 percent five years ago and 278 percent in 
1987 the christian democrats 331 percent down from 35 percent 
five years ago and 342 percent in 1987 and the socialists 154 
percent up from 133 percent and 143 percent respectively 
premier giulio andreotti a christian democrat had said that 
major shifts in the voting could cause his government to collapse 
the coalition includes three small parties republicans social 
democrats and liberals 
