slepak said he never expected he would one day protest against the 
israeli government 
in the soviet union we knew there was one party and we knew 
what they would do but here nobody knows what will be tomorrow 
said slepak who arrived in israel after waging a long fight 
against soviet authorities for permission to emigrate 
rally organizers accused politicians of abusing democracy and 
demanded that president chaim herzog appoint an independent 
commission to work out a new electoral system 
the campaign led by dozens of israeli mayors and army reserve 
officers has collected more than a halfmillion signatures 
under israels current system voters choose party slates and 
the country is treated as one electoral district a party needs 
only one percent of the vote to win a seat in the 120member 
parliament no party has ever won enough votes to rule alone and 
smaller factions are often cast in the role of kingmaker 
israelis are used to protracted coalition negotiations after 
each election but this time neither labor nor likud appears able 
to break a 6060 tie 
labor leader shimon peres failed after five weeks of 
negotiations and now caretaker prime minister yitzhak shamir is 
trying to form a ruling coalition without labor 
but shamirs plans have been thwarted by two religious parties 
the national religious party and shas that support shamir in 
principle but insist that he form another government with labor 
under the national religious partys compromise a new 
likudlabor coalition would be based on the guidelines of the 
outgoing government including shamirs proposal to hold elections 
in the occupied west bank and gaza strip to determine negotiators 
for peace talks with israel 
but decisions concerning the peace process would be made by the 
full 25member cabinet which also includes ministers from smaller 
coalition partners 
in the outgoing government such decisions were made by the 
12member inner cabinet in which only labor and likud were 
represented the forum was usually deadlocked along party lines 
