<TEXT>
lotte jacobi a photographer known for her 
candid portraits of such renowed figures as albert einstein and 
eleanor roosevelt has died at age 93 
jacobi died sunday at the havenwood retirement community the 
cause of death wasnt disclosed 
during her career which spanned seven decades celebrities 
sought out jacobi because of her ability to capture them during 
private moments or in unusual poses 
some of her most famous photographs were of einstein including 
at least one that was turned down by life magazine because its 
editors thought the shot of einstein lounging in a leather jacket 
did not treat him with enough respect 
other portraits included mrs roosevelt poet robert frost 
actors peter lorre and lotte lenya and composer kurt weill 
jacobi said she relied on her intuition for knowing whom to 
photograph and how to photograph them 
most people have a preconceived idea about other people about 
what the other one has to be she said in an interview in 1978 
i dont care for a persons station in life i care for the 
person 
jacobi was born in thorn west prussia germany in 1896 and 
studied at the bavarian state academy of photography and the 
university of munich she moved to berlin in 1920 where she later 
ran her fathers photography studio 
in 1935 she fled nazi germany and moved to new york where she 
opened her own studio 
later in her career jacobi invented a type of photography known 
as photogenics a technique that did not require use of a camera 
jacobi would draw patterns of light on film using reflected light 
from candles and flashlights she then would photograph the 
resulting lines and images of light 
jacobi moved to new hampshire in 1955 and opened a studio in 
deering she became active in state and national democratic 
politics and was visited by many presidential candidates as they 
trekked to new hampshire for its earliestinthenation primary 
jacobi had lived at the havenwood retirement community since 
1985 
she is survived by a sister ruth jacobiroth of california and 
two daughtersinlaw bernadette hunter of paris france and 
beatrice trumhunter of deering 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

