<TEXT>
someone tried to decapitate the 
little mermaid the beloved bronze fairytale figure in copenhagen 
harbor and danish detectives on monday were trying to figure out 
who and why 
they even assigned a homicide cop to the case 
the 7inch cut in the back of the statues neck apparently made 
with a hacksaw was discovered monday by an engineering student 
police said 
the 76yearold statue built in tribute to danish storyteller 
hans christian andersen depicts a winsome girlsized mermaid 
gazing pensively over the water from her perch atop a rock 
the little mermaids tale is one of andersens bestloved and 
the statue within stepping distance of the shore along langelinie 
quay is something of a danish national symbol about 500000 
tourists visit it each year 
