bluegreen deposits in the gash indicated the attempt was made at 
least several days ago analysts were trying to pinpoint the time 
but so many people touch the statue that fingerprints arent 
likely to provide clues christensen said 
tourists and locals alike in their customary cluster at the 
quay were indignant 
its again a mad person who did this said ejnar weikop a 
dane 
oh no not again said audrey bates of sydney australia 
this is ridiculous 
the little mermaid has been the target of vandals before the 
original head was stolen in 1964 it was replaced by a new one cast 
from the original mold 
in 1984 an arm was taken but it was found and reattached the 
mermaid has also been marred by graffiti and paint and one 
prankster painted a pink brassiere on her 
