a strong earthquake occurred monday night in 
the pacific ocean off panama the us geological survey reported 
spokesman don finley said monitors did not believe the quake was 
strong enough to cause significant damage on land or major ocean 
surface disturbance 
the tremor was centered about 250 miles southwest of panama 
city about 100 miles south of puerto armuelles or 120 miles 
southwest of santiago it occured at 802 pm edt which is also 
802 pm panama time 
survey monitors at golden colo said they recorded the quake 
at an estimated 62 magnitude on the richter scale according to 
finley 
the quake was reported felt in veraguas province and in the city 
of santiago 
the center of the quake was given as latitude 69 north 
longitude 827 west 
every increase of one number on the richter scale corresponds to 
an increase of 10 times in the ground motion 
on land a quake of 65 can cause severe damage in builtup 
areas the san francisco earthquake of last october was computed to 
be a 71 magnitude quake 
