<TEXT>
ralph clark a former publisher and 
general manager of the grand island independent died sunday from 
parkinsons disease at age 79 
clark entered the newspaper business at the age of 13 in 1923 
he was a linotype operator and printer on several kansas and 
nebraska weeklies later he became an ad manager at augusta and 
larned kan and was ad manager of the weekly columbus neb news 
for five years before coming to grand island 
clark served as an advertising salesman at the independent for 
six years became advertising manager in 1949 and general manager 
in 1963 he also served as publisher in his final years of 
management 
he was credited with guiding the newspaper from hot metal type 
to offset type in 1974 he retired in 1977 
