<TEXT>
not since the 1970s have newspaper 
advertising sales been so slow and no quick recovery is in sight 
from times mirror cos firstquarter earnings slump company chief 
robert f erburu said may 3 
we are experiencing the impact of a very weak economy in the 
northeast and midatlantic area erburu times mirrors board 
chairman and chief executive told shareholders at the companys 
annual meeting 
he said times mirror whose flagship is the los angeles times 
was making hundreds of millions of dollars in capital investments 
at the hartford conn courant the newsday editions on long 
island ny and in new york city and the baltimore sun 
newspapers 
those investments wont pay off until the economy recovers he 
said 
the most one can say is that 1990 is proving to be a very 
difficult year and the future course of the economy will be a key 
factor in our outcome erburu said 
times mirror said last week that its firstquarter profits fell 
33 percent to 46 million largely because of slow advertising at 
its northeastern papers consumer magazines and broadcast 
television operations 
the firstquarter falloff was felt through much of the industry 
on may 3 the washington post co said weak advertising pushed 
profits down 6 percent to 39 million even gannett co where 
earnings had grown nonstop for more than two decades had only a 
slight profit gain from 749 million to 75 million gannett 
revenue fell 1 percent to 8134 million 
erburu made his remarks in the times new 230 million olympic 
plant east of downtown where stateoftheart presses can churn 
out a 96page paper with 24 pages in full color the times also is 
modernizing printing plants in orange county and the san fernando 
valley spending 405 million in all 
in an interview erburu said the company is looking for more 
fresh ideas such as its partnership with kcaltv to produce 
4minute orange county news summaries to be inserted into cnns 
headline news every halfhour the summaries drawing on stories 
from times reporters will be shown by times mirrors cable company 
in orange county 
