kidnapped march 16 1985 he was cited by the nbna for his 
outstanding contributions to the field of broadcast journalism 
the charnley award is given annually to a journalist with 
midwestern ties who has distinguished himself in the broadcast 
industry anderson spent three years as a radio and television 
reporter at krnt and kccitv in des moines iowa before joining 
the ap in detroit in may 1974 
the award established in 1968 is named for mitchell v 
charnley professor emeritus from the university of minnesota 
school of journalism and mass communication charnley taught at the 
university from 1934 to 1968 and was a founder of the nbna 
