faced with a flood of phone calls and 
facsimile messages claiming responsibility for terrorist attacks 
colombias news media are beginning to ignore the messages 
the reason is simple it is impossible to tell who is really on 
the other end of the line drug traffickers police posing as drug 
traffickers leftist guerrillas pranskters 
until a few weeks ago virtually all of colombias radio 
stations and newspapers used the statements without question no 
one pointed out the information came from anonymous people and 
could not be verified 
recently the countrys two leading newspapers bogotas el 
espectador and el tiempo chose not to publish news about some of 
the anonymous messages 
an example of the confusion came after leftist presidential 
candidate carlos pizarro was killed april 26 by an assassin on a 
colombian airliner 
within two hours the anonymous telephone calls started 
it was the medellin cartel one man said another president 
would be assassinated he said 
the next day brought another facsimile message also supposedly 
from the medellin cartel to a bogota radio station caracol 
it wasnt us the supposed cartel communique said it accused 
the police of killing people and setting off bombs so that the 
cartel would be blamed 
another example came after a truck bomb in medellin killed 20 
people on april 11 
