<TEXT>
bill seidman can be a hard man to get along 
with but the white house may find hes even harder to get along 
without 
seidman has been both a leading man and a lightning rod in the 
savings and loan bailout while his policy dissents have made the 
administration uncomfortable his role provided political 
insulation president bush will lose that when seidman leaves 
probably in the fall 
therell be no argument over the credentials of william taylor 
the federal reserve boards bank supervisor to take over seidmans 
dual role as chairman of the federal deposit insurance corp and 
the resolution trust corp and he is likely to prove as independent 
as seidman 
but taylor will be a lot quieter about it 
seidman l william is the name on the letterhead is out 
front outspoken a very public public figure 
thats made him a popular man in congress and with the news 
media and an irksome one to some people in the administration 
among them the high command at the treasury and white house chief 
of staff john sununu 
seidman now 69 was appointed to the fdic post by president 
reagan for a term that runs until october 1991 and the franchise 
was expanded when congress passed the savings and loan bailout bill 
last year the fdic now insures both bank and savings and loan 
depositors and the resolution trust corp sells the assets of 
failing sampls closed by the government 
the chairman is appointed by the president and confirmed by the 
senate for a sixyear term once hes there hes independent the 
president cant oust him 
but there are ways seidman had said he planned to leave before 
his term was up and hoped he could do so after getting the sampl 
rescue effort off to a good beginning he also had sounded alarms 
about rising costs complained about bureaucratic delays in the 
bailout and dismissed some administration suggestions sometimes 
with a wisecrack 
and so there appeared in the washington post on may day a report 
that seidman had met with bush in midapril had said he wasnt 
going to complete his full term and had been encouraged to end it 
sooner rather than later 
from that point the script was predictable when a president 
wants somebody to leave the government it is customary that he 
praises the mans performance and says that he respects the 
fellows wish to move on 
seidman knows the way it works hes been around republican 
politics for more than 30 years and he served in the white house as 
an economic aide to president ford 
bill has indicated that hes not going to stay the whole term 
and we are interested in getting new leadership there that will 
