you do not solve these problems by shooting the messenger 
said rep bruce f vento dminn who heads a house task force on 
the rtc 
hey listen bush countered if all the people that 
brought bad news in here were asked to do something else it would 
be a little lonely 
bush said seidman had done a good job with grace and ability 
and had made his own decision to leave and he also said look 
i understand if you might want to put your own person in there 
the president said thursday its his initiative with me and 
today he suggested the name of a bill taylor who were very high on 
to take over 
the president inherited the savings and loan crisis and made the 
rescue bailout bill one of his earliest priorities the initial 
cost estimate was 257 billion thats now up to at least 325 
billion and probably more the general accounting office says the 
price could be 500 billion over 30 years 
thats too costly not to become a political issue at some point 
that may be hastened by seidmans departure its an inherited 
