<TEXT>
 
detroit ap good nutrition is just what the doctor ordered 
for nearly 850000 detroit residents 
theyre enrolled in the focus hope food prescription program 
one of the oldest and biggest supplemental food programs for people 
in highrisk groups lowincome pregnant and postpartum women 
their children up to age 6 and the elderly 
each month participants push grocery carts down the aisles of 
one of five focus hope food centers stocking up on milk fruit 
meat butter vegetables cheese cereal rice dried beans peanut 
butter instant potatoes egg mix and juice 
there are six food prescriptions depending on a 
participants age having filled the appropriate one the shopper 
then passes through a checkout counter complete with a barcode 
scanner to speed things up 
similar foods are available to qualified people in two dozen 
cities under the commodity supplemental food program of the us 
department of agriculture 
but in detroit we do things differently says eleanor 
josaitis who cofounded focus hope a civil and human rights 
organization in the aftermath of the 1967 riots 
one difference in the detroit program is how it looks 
focus hope food centers resemble grocery stores we try to 
set things up where people can come in get their carts and do 
their own shopping josaitis says 
if a mother comes into the food center with a small child and 
pushes a shopping cart that child may see his mother as just going 
to the grocery store she may not have a lot of choices but if she 
wants to pick one item over another green beans say instead of 
corn she can do that its a small thing but its a symbol of 
dignity of how we like to treat people 
the food centers also are equipped with closedcircuit 
televisions that run ads encouraging people to look into other 
focus hope programs such as employment training housing day 
care and education 
agencies in a number of cities have modeled programs after 
detroits says josaitis who held a national conference two years 
ago to share information about its principles and design 
the food packages designed by a dietician are intended as 
supplements although infants are given a full months supply of 
formula the usda buys the food 
by using the national purchasing power we can provide food to 
three times as many people says josaitis she says 846613 
people filled food prescriptions last year when the program began 
in 1971 it served 85058 
senior citizens with incomes up to 130 percent of poverty 
7774 for a oneperson household and women with incomes up to 
185 percent of poverty 11063 for one are eligible 
once accepted each participant is entitled to six monthly trips 
to the food center they then must be rescreened by the state 
health department or a private doctor if their condition is 
unchanged they continue on the program another six months 
a network of 40000 volunteers provides transportation or food 
delivery to those who need it it also builds awareness of the 
hunger problem 
i believe you have to be touched by it says josaitis if 
people dont see or feel an injustice they cant be part of the 
solution 
</TEXT>
