editors note in the early days they had to be registered 
nurses then they had to be young and pretty now with the aircraft 
cabin graying as one said the nations flight attendants are 
fighting weight restrictions 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
there was a time when airline stewardesses were fired if they 
turned 32 got married became pregnant or had to put on eyeglasses 
stewardesses are called flight attendants now in deference to 
men who have joined their ranks and many of the restrictive rules 
have been dumped as a result of antidiscrimination laws and 
lawsuits 
some flight attendants however still are being fired for 
weighing too much 
at american airlines the nations largest employer of flight 
attendants the union is suing the company and challenging some of 
the industrys most stringent weight requirements 
the association of professional flight attendants the union for 
americans 16000 attendants says the 37yearold weight 
guidelines are an extension of age and sex discrimination 
the union contends they hearken to the coffee tea or me era 
when sexy young stewardesses were marketing tools congress had 
not yet outlawed age and sex discrimination 
national airlines urged travelers to fly me im cheryl 
braniffs sky girls wore hot pants and continental promised we 
move our tails for you 
now union officials call it an irrational and cruel policy that 
forces women in their 40s and 50s to weigh what they did when they 
were 21 
they say attendants sometimes resort to crash diets 
liposuction breast reductions and drug use and some develop 
eating disorders in an effort to stay trim 
we truly believe the flying public wants professional 
efficient and wellgroomed flight attendants safe airplanes and 
ontime service said tommie huttoblake a flight attendant from 
ridgewood nj and former union president we dont think the 
public cares if a flight attendant wears a size 6 or a size 10 
union members are wearing buttons urging patrons to weigh my 
job performance not my body billboards with similar messages 
are going up outside airports 
both sides are girding for a 1991 trial date in federal court in 
fort worth texas 
in april the federal equal employment opportunity commission 
joined the flight attendants battle filing a federal classaction 
suit in us district court in los angeles the lawsuit charges the 
weight policy discriminates against women particularly those over 
40 
american still wants their flight attendants to appeal to a 
male sexist notion of what is sexy said eeoc lawyer ralph dh 
fertig and thats thin 
he said americans policy reads that a firm trim silhouette 
free of bulges rolls or paunches is necessary for an alert 
efficient image 
we believe its in our rights to have an appropriate grooming 
standard for our employees said american spokesman ed stewart 
we want a neat attractive person representing american 
union lawyer kathleen king of san francisco said the job has 
changed since the 1950s when women like her mother became flight 
attendants on a lark before settling down and getting married 
youve got flight attendants with 20 and 25 years of seniority 
who are being thrown out the door because theyre a few pounds 
overweight she said 
last year pan american world airways ended six years of 
litigation by raising weight requirements and allowing an extra 9 
pounds as flight attendants age pan am also agreed to pay 23 
million in lost wages to 115 employees who were not allowed to work 
because of their weight 
other carriers including delta airlines and usair have less 
stringent weight charts delta and trans world airlines allow 
considerable leeway in pounds for aging flight attendants 
united airlines is proposing dropping its weight regulations 
northwest and continental have already done so 
americans weight standards are roughly tied to a 1959 
metropolitan life insurance co chart at american a 5foot5inch 
attendant may weigh no more than 129 pounds 
the same employee could weigh up to 138 pounds at delta with 4 
added pounds as she ages and up to 150 pounds at pan am plus an 
additional 9 pounds as she ages at united airlines she could 
weigh up to 137 pounds plus an extra 9 pounds as she ages 
american airlines weight guidelines were modified slightly in 
1975 after a court challenge but the union argues that 80 percent 
of the flight attendants were under 35 then american dismisses the 
argument that a woman inevitably gains weight with age children or 
menopause 
american airlines president robert crandall during a recent 
speech to about 500 employees in new york was confronted by ms 
huttoblake 
were not all young thin employees today she told him 
there has been a graying of the cabin 
by her side stood doris johnson 46 of new york who was 
suspended without pay in september after 17 years of flying she is 
5feet4 139 pounds wears a size 9 shoe has undergone a 
hysterectomy and has spent a decade fighting to stay below 125 
pounds to keep her job 
i must say in looking at you im surprised you dont look 
like you have a weight problem crandall told ms johnson she 
took a demotion last week to a ground position to avoid being fired 
but crandall insists weight standards are necessary weve got 
some people on our airplanes that are way too heavy 
in los angeles 28year veteran patt gibbs took a fouryear 
leave to become union president upon her return the 5foot3inch 
ms gibbs was 154 pounds 29 pounds over her limit 
it was pretty humiliating she said they said thats 
that youre too heavy lose the weight or you wont have a job 
she lost the weight and returned to work 
also in los angeles sherri cappello was fired the day she 
received her 25year service pin 
in march she was elected vice president by the largest number 
of votes in the unions history some measure of how the 
rankandfile think about weight standards 
in wisconsin after flying 43 years petey peterson retired two 
years before turning 65 and getting a full pension she was in the 
berlin airlift received american airlines award of valor and was 
among the last of those who started in days when flight attendants 
had to be registered nurses 
i was forced into early retirement because i could no longer 
fit the image and take the harassment of the flight attendant 
weight program as enforced by my 29yearold supervisor she says 
