<TEXT>
richard beymer says he had no idea how rotten 
his character would become when he was cast as the kingpin of abcs 
twin peaks 
beymer plays business entrepreneur benjamin horne in director 
david lynchs new series that offers a quirky blend of soap opera 
murder mystery and black comedy 
he says johanna ray the casting director had originally 
considered him for the role of the psychiatrist the part russ 
tamblyn plays then lynch suggested he could be benjamin horne 
i had no idea now nefarious and slimy he was going to be 
beymer says every time i got a new script he was doing this or 
that its like waking up one morning and finding yourself an arch 
villain isnt that a nightmare 
horne owns the great northern hotel a department store and 
other properties but is also conspiring with catherine packard 
martell piper laurie to acquire the packard sawmill 
the show centers on the murder of laura palmer a high school 
homecoming queen who had a mysterious link to virtually everyone in 
the picturesque lumber mill town of twin peaks near the 
washingtoncanadian border each episode slowly reveals the dirty 
secrets of its characters 
twin peaks is an acting comeback for beymer whose career 
faltered after youthful starring roles in such hit films as west 
side story and the diary of anne frank he worked mostly as a 
film editor cinematographer and filmmaker before returning to 
acting in the 1980s 
beymer was born in iowa but his family moved here when he was a 
child he began working on a local television show when he was 10 
at 13 he was in so big and went to rome for indiscretions of 
an american wife he was in diary of anne frank when he was 
19 and west side story two years later 
this summer beymer will direct a theatrical movie based on his 
adaptation of michael wolks novel the big picture 
i did four or five films after west side story beymer 
says i didnt quit things changed i went to new york and got 
into the actors studio with the encouragement of joanne woodward 
id been in pictures with joanne and paul newman and eli wallach 
and i had never studied acting 
then in early 1964 i became socially conscious and went to 
mississippi for the voter registration drive it struck me as a 
wonderful thing to document i bought a 16mm bolex camera and 
filmed everything i saw i brought the film back to los angeles and 
spent the next nine months editing it 
the documentary which became a regular bouquet was 
narrated by robert ryan it was shown on the pbs series eyes on 
the prize 
beymer later made educational films and spent six years on a 
film called innerview 
in 1984 he had a starring role in the abc series paper dolls 
thankfully they canceled it he says i ran a sportswear 
fashion company i was ready for it to be over after 13 shows it 
was totally about hair and makeup and glamour 
beymer says he wants to film the big picture as 
inconspicuously as possible in new york city he wrote the 
screenplay and will direct but will not appear in it he says the 
title will be changed because another movie has the same title 
the process is what interests me he says im not 
interested in going out with trucks and hair and makeup and 
creating a big circus i want a film that uses real people and 
integrates real situations into the film hollywood films focus on 
the star you dont get to know anyone else 
the main character in the big picture is max popper who 
writes pornography to support his other writing and becomes caught 
up in a murder 
it takes place around times square where all those wonderful 
old movie houses now show porno films 
