<TEXT>
carl icahn took his battle with usx corp 
management to the companys annual meeting today but the corporate 
raider conceded that his plan to split the steelenergy giant in 
two could fail 
icahn usxs biggest shareholder disclosed the pessimism as he 
urged other stockholders to approve his proposal for separating the 
companys healthier marathon oil co subsidiary from its laggard 
us steel business 
about 600 shareholders packed a junior high school auditorium in 
findlay marathons hometown to hear icahn and usx management 
present their views on how to shape the future of one of the 
biggest us industrial corporations 
the vote on icahns plan is widely seen as a test of how much 
influence corporate takeover strategists still have now that much 
of the muscle to back up their threats billions of dollars in 
financing has atrophied because of a severe decline in their war 
chest the market for high risk junk bonds 
results of the vote arent expected for at least a week but 
icahn who has 133 percent of usx shares or about 34 million 
shares admitted as the meeting began that he might not have the 
crucial support needed from five or six large institutional 
investors about 200 million shares were expected to be voted 
these large institutions whom icahn didnt identify preferred 
to allow management to do it on their own he told shareholders 
under icahns plan 80 percent of us steel would be spun off 
as a dividend to shareholders each shareholder would own stock in 
us steel and marathon that icahn estimated would be worth a 
combined value of 48 
the unlikelihood of approval evidently depressed usxs stock 
price late this morning shares were trading at 3350 on the new 
york stock exchange down 50 cents from friday 
several shareholders objected to icahns plan and backed usx 
chairman charles corry who wants to keep both steel and energy 
under one roof the antiicahn shareholders said they want usx to 
remain intact so the steel and energy businesses could support each 
other when one wasnt doing well 
corry also contended that the steel businesss profitability had 
improved in recent years and that he too was frustrated by the 
companys relatively low stock price nonetheless he told 
shareholders the real question is would the specific icahn 
proposal address that 
icahns comments generally were met with polite appluse but 
shareholders calling for the defeat of his proposal got a larger 
hand from the gathering 
the meeting today was preceded by an intense lobbying effort by 
both sides to woo shareholders 
its disappointing when a management appears to reject a 
program that could do nothing but benefit all shareholders icahn 
said in an open letter in newspapers to corry last week corry 
respnded with his own open letter calling icahns proposal is 
flawed and is neither cost nor tax efficient 
even if icahns proposal doesnt garner a majority analysts who 
have followed the company and the takeover business in general 
speculated usx would have to respond if his plan received a 
substantial number of votes 
icahn chairman of trans world airlines is a veteran of wars 
with management at usx and other big companies and has learned he 
can win even in defeat he lost a fight to unseat the board of 
texaco inc two years ago but the oil giant later restructured and 
he took home a 3386 million dividend 
the usx vote represents a test of sorts on the future of 
takeover strategists stymied by a lack of financing since the 
collapse of the junk bond market last fall wouldbe dealmakers and 
corporate raiders have returned to proxy votes and shareholder 
proposals to seek control of companies or a bigger voice in 
management 
a clear loss for icahn would place into doubt how much power a 
strategist has these days 
