the major aerospace companies of france and britain 
will team up to develop a supersonic passenger plane with greater 
speed capacity and range than their existing concorde according 
to a report published monday 
la tribune a parisbased financial newspaper said the accord 
between privately owned british aerospace plc and frances 
aerospatiale which is owned by the government would be announced 
wednesday 
aerospatiale confirmed an important agreement would be 
announced in paris on wednesday regarding a new supersonic 
airplane but it declined to give other details 
the project would cost between 85 billion and 135 billion 
according to la tribune it would require about five years of 
research and take eight years to manufacture the newspaper said 
international aviation experts agreed that the next generation 
of supersonic passenger planes would need to carry at least 200 
people at speeds of mach 25 or 2 times the speed of sound on 
flights up of to 7460 the concordes developed in the mid1970s 
carry about 110 people at mach 2 twice the speed of sound and 
have a range of about 3730 miles 
aerospatiale announced monday that it has agreed to expand 
cooperation with the statecontrolled italian group selenia 
industrie elettroniche associate spa to cover all areas of their 
missile operations 
