gain from the initial public offering of lyondell petrochemical 
co although that was partially offset by 345 million in charges 
for future environmental and other expenses 
in this years quarter arco adopted new accounting procedures 
resulting in a 323 million reduction in its deferred tax 
liability however that was partially offset by 233 million in 
charges for expenses such as future cleanups it said 
excluding those onetime considerations earnings would have 
risen 10 percent to 457 million from 415 million due to 
improving prices for crude oil and refined products and higher 
natural gas sales arco chairman lodwrick m cook said 
aftertax quarterly earnings for worldwide oil and gas 
operations rose 64 percent to 319 million from 195 million 
