<TEXT>
a wall street broker his lawyer brother and a 
third man have been indicted on federal charges of perjury and 
obstruction of justice stemming from a 17 million embezzlement 
scheme prosecutors said 
a grand jury last week indicted the trio and a fourth individual 
in a case that prosecutors say dates back to 1980 and involved 
attempts to conceal both the laundering of checks and income tax 
evasion 
the indictment was announced by the us attorneys office 
monday and the men are scheduled to be arraigned tuesday 
the checks according to the indictment represented about 16 
million that had been embezzled from bankers trust co by other 
individuals plus nearly 95000 in stock loan fees 
three people pleaded guilty previously to the embezzlement and 
were given probation said jeff fardella assistant us attorney 
the new defendants are accused of having tried to obstruct that 
investigation in part by falsely claiming that dead or 
nonexistent persons had been the source of the money 
named in the indictment are joseph j stella a former vice 
president and manager of the stock loan department of bear stearns 
amp co inc his brother fred c stella a lawyer and roger c 
capozzi sr 
the indictment charges all three with one count of conspiracy to 
obstruct justice in addition fred stella was charged with five 
counts of obstructing justice and capozzi with three counts of 
perjury and three counts of obstructing justice 
the fourth defendant joseph a pontarelli jr was accused of 
income tax evasion and filing a false tax return according to 
fardella 
bear stearns was not involved in the case 
</TEXT>
